A woman has appeared in court charged with murder following the death of a 63-year-old who was found seriously injured in a common close.Police were called to the scene in Glen Avenue, Port Glasgow, Inverclyde, at around 12.10am on Tuesday.The injured 63-year-old woman was taken to Inverclyde Royal Hospital in Greenock, where she died a short time after admission.Sadie Bell, 33, was charged with murder when she appeared at Greenock Sheriff Court yesterday.She made no plea or declaration and was remanded in custody.